.TH "alloc_lpt_leb" 9 "alloc_lpt_leb" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
alloc_lpt_leb \- allocate an LPT LEB that is empty.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" alloc_lpt_leb
.BI "(struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "int *lnum "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "lnum" 12
LEB number is passed and returned here
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function finds the next empty LEB in the ltab starting from \fIlnum\fP. If a
an empty LEB is found it is returned in \fIlnum\fP and the function returns 0.
Otherwise the function returns -ENOSPC.  Note however, that LPT is designed
never to run out of space.
